						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone near the temple of Kōḍi Basappa.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged record states that <hi rend="bold">Sāveya-Nāyaka,</hi> (son of) <hi rend="bold">Chavuḍādēvi</hi> set up a hero-stone in memory of a hero called <hi rend="bold">Manaya-Nāyaka</hi> who died for his master <hi rend="bold">Chavuṁḍeya-Nāyaka</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Mallūr.</hi> <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Mādarasa</hi> is mentioned. He is stated to be a devotee of <hi rend="bold">Dhavaḷanātha of Kālaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>The characters are of about <hi rend="bold">13th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
